<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='377000' id='t-377000'>(Applause)</span>
</span>
</p>
<p class='talk-transcript__para'>
<data class='talk-transcript__para__time'>
 6:33
</data>
<span class='talk-transcript__para__text'>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='382000' id='t-382000'>This kind of work is also very much like puppetry,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='387000' id='t-387000'>where the found object is, in a sense, the puppet,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='391000' id='t-391000'>and I'm the puppeteer at first, because I'm playing with an object.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='396000' id='t-396000'>But then I make the machine, which is sort of the stand-in for me,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='400000' id='t-400000'>and it is able to achieve the action that I want.</span>
</span>
